(10p+q)+(10q+p)&=11(p+q)
\end{align*}. Given the problem statement, we also know that $p+q=13$. Plugging this into our previous equation yields $(10p+q)+(10q+p)=11\cdot 13=143$. The question asks us for the value of $(10p+q)+(10q+p)$, which is equal to 143. The answer is: 143.
